HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 217
By Butler
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Lily Shelton on her
receipt of the Governor's Volunteer Stars Award.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those estimable citizens who have dedicated their time and energies to helping
others; and
WHEREAS, each year, 1.3 million Tennessee volunteers give over 99 million hours of
community service, contributing $2.6 billion to Tennessee's economy; and
WHEREAS, these volunteers are the backbone of our communities, and by donating
their time and talents to fulfill needs that would otherwise go unmet, they embody the spirit of
giving; and
WHEREAS, Lily Shelton of Anderson County is one such exemplary person, who is a
recipient of the Governor's Volunteer Stars Award in recognition of her laudable commitment to
her community; and
WHEREAS, through her leadership positions as president of the Interact Club and class
president for both her junior and senior years, Ms. Shelton sets a strong example for her peers;
and
WHEREAS, Lily Shelton emphasizes impactful leadership, and she provides guidance
and inspiration for her peers, encouraging classmates to take on leadership roles themselves;
and
WHEREAS, Ms. Shelton is a model citizen; her commitment to helping others through
volunteerism epitomizes the spirit of the Volunteer State, and she should be specially
recognized; now, therefore,
